properties.headline: Special Weather Statement issued January 8 at 10:35AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
..THE ENHANCED LANDSLIDE THREAT IN WESTERN WASHINGTON WILL DIMINISH
OVER THE NEXT TWO DAYS...

Soil moisture will remain at high levels across western Washington
with an attendant enhanced threat for landslides. The threat will
slowly diminishing over the next two days since there is little
additional rainfall expected. Therefore this alert will be allowed
to expire this afternoon, though there is always a slight potential
for landslides while the soils remain wet.

As many as a half dozen landslides have already been reported in
various locations in western Washington.

For more information about current conditions, visit
www.weather.gov/seattle, select Hydrology, and then scroll down for
the links to the landslide information pages.

For more information on landslides, visit the website for the
Washington State Department of Natural Resources landslide
geologic hazards at: http://bit.ly/2mtA3wn
